        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 5:26PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 526 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Lake Waccamaw, or 16 miles east of Whiteville,
moving southwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Waccamaw, Makatoka, Freeman, Honey Island, Exum, Delco, Crusoe
Island, Bolton, and Sandy Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
southeastern North Carolina.</instruction>
